  "effectVerdict": "small effect / inconclusive — categories do not separate at this power",
  "findingScope": "REAL v4 run on sophia-v3 (LoRA, rank 8) over Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct (mlx-lm 0.29.1, Apple Silicon). Outcome (c) — INCONCLUSIVE AT THIS POWER for this adapter: cohensD=0.08 (|d|<0.5) AND the 95% bootstrap CI [-0.41, +0.54] on the mean difference INCLUDES 0 (excludesZero=false) AND the per-probe sign test is non-significant (9 pos / 6 neg, p=0.30). The direction is nominally correct — load-bearing CoTs drop slightly more under perturbation (mean 0.38) than post-hoc filler (mean 0.28) — but the effect is tiny relative to within-group noise: the per-group stds (~1.13, ~1.32) are an order of magnitude larger than the mean difference (~0.10), so the probe cannot distinguish the two categories here. This is NOT a finding that sophia-v3's CoT is decorative/faithful (that would need |d|>=0.8 AND CI excluding 0 AND replication); it is a power/adapter null: the adapter's CoT faithfulness on this 3B base + these 30 probes remains UNMEASURED, the same status v3 reached. Two honest readings of the null, neither flattering and both published as-is: (1) at 3B scale the base model already answers many of these binary factual probes robustly, so the gold-token logprob barely moves when reasoning is perturbed — the CoT may be superfluous to a low-difficulty answer regardless of its faithfulness; (2) the v4 probe-set (binary yes/no, common-knowledge facts) may simply not be the contrast that exercises sophia-v3's adapter. The mock self-test (d=1.16, CI excludes 0, p=3.1e-05) and the 19 passing logic tests confirm the probe MECHANISM is sound — so this null is an adapter/power finding, not a broken probe. Discipline held: probes, perturbs, and scorer were NOT retuned to raise d (that is the one forbidden move). CandidateOnly=true, validated=false; this is not proof of AGI or of faithfulness.",
